content:
When a form messaging component is sent in a messaging session, your customer has 5 minutes by default to submit their responses before the link expires. You can now customize this limit for each form.

This change applies to enhanced Messaging channels and Messaging for In-App and Web. On the Messaging Components page in Setup, click a form name to open the Messaging Component Builder. Click the Customization tab on the left, enter your expiration limit for the form, and click Save.

After a form link expires, the customer canâ€™t submit their responses. However, agents or automation can send them the form again.
title: Customizing Secure Form Expiration in Messaging Sessions
